The number of new HIV infections has been declining since 2007.
In 2011, there were about 2700 cases.
That's about a tenth less than the year before.
What symptoms indicate an STD?
The infectious diseases can cause genital ulcers, urinary discomfort, discharge, abdominal pain, and blisters or warts.
However, they often do not cause pain or other symptoms and therefore go unnoticed.
How can you protect yourself?
Condoms can reduce the risk of infection, but they do not offer 100% protection.
Because some STDs can also be transmitted through contact with the skin and close physical contact.
